node.title: Latest: Omicron cases rise to 13, Baker wants border to stay shut to keep new variant out
node.content: ["New Zealand recorded five more cases of the new coronavirus variant Omicron on Sunday, taking the total number to 13 in the country.", "Four of the new cases remain in managed isolation with one now recovered and released.", "The recovered case arrived from London via Singapore on 7 December and tested positive to COVID-19 on their day 0/1 test.", "The ministry said that the case was never in the community while infectious.", "What you need to know:"]
